The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 May is 276,033 (31,814.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 May, there were 894 new confirmed cases (103.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 May, there were 946 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 5% (52 fewer cases).
